	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If it aint broke dont fix it.<BR>
<BR>
 The game is about the player having fun, not how balanced the game is. If people are having fun and saying not to nerf clerics anymore and there are no objections from the players well then... who cares if they think its unbalanced if the players are happy. Instead of making rangers a more useful class (in terms of battles. Track is very useful BTW.) and necro better for raids (lots of dragons and stuff go off disease so they cant lifetap to get converted hp to mana back verant makes a very useful, relativly boring class and makes them *LESS* useful (totally and less are many times confused.). People want clerics for their heals. Their buffs are nice but if you really were lookin for buffs you would get a shaman. People spend 100s of hours getting those breastplates only to be nerfed and with no compensation. People got that bp and gave away their others for the stats *AND* effect, to take that away from them with no real compensation is ridiculous. <BR>
 Absor and Abashi have and will probably use the argument &quot;why would we do this to our own game? it makes no sense.&quot; to tell the truth I dont know why they would do that to their game. People were happy it was going ok (well maybe not as happy as they were but happy enough) but people were punished for their achievements. If FoH or who ever kills dragons in the sleeper's tomb before you wanted them well then dont under estimate their ability as a player and guild. If players are killing &quot;uber&quot; mobs too fast then MAKE THE MOB STRONGER! you most likely will say that this forces people to pull together and use teamwork, they have! Its actually kinda better that they can do certian raids with less people. creates less looting BS (all to common in larger groups) AND CREATES LESS LAG! some people fear trakanon, some people fear Venril Sathir, some people fear raid lag and not being able to join raids because an overwhelming amount of people have to go on the raid to get the job done. <BR>
   I truly believe if you let players report the unbalances of certian items/classes abilities (not VI staff members) then you would make alot more people happy and if people notice a problem they wont mind as much as if you say there may be a problem in the future. People want proof, proof you cant show them. The game balances mean NOTHING as long as the customers are happy, playing and in bulk. Dont make changes that &quot;balance&quot; the game if the actual players dont want them. YOUR check comes out of OUR pockets. We're happy and getting over a bad nerf on clerics and then you do this? You wanna save this great game? dont do something you know the players wont like and think of as a challenge. As long as the players are happy it shouldnt matter, Rangers want to go up on the useful list not have everyone else pulled down with them.<BR>
<BR>
    What really saddens me is that nor absor nor abshi nor anyone who can e-mail this to them will see it. I said it once and i'll say it again...<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
      DONT FIX IT IF IT AINT BROKE!
				</font>
