	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a cleric twink that I play now and then... but nerfs like this don't exactly encourage me to play him more.... If Verant keeps this up, there will only be three classes played in the game. Clerics, Enchanters and Warriors and I am beginning to think that clerics will be replaced with Druids. After all, Druids have almost as good healing ability at the really high levels (especially if they get Celestial Healing like I am hearing that they will) and can do SO much more (buff, evac, etc) that a cleric can't do.<BR>
<BR>
As bad as Clerics are getting nerfed, there are classes that have it worse. Type the following command sometime:<BR>
<BR>
/who all wizard 40 50<BR>
<BR>
You might get like 3 to 5 on average... maybe a smidge more during primetime. Now try the following commands to see how ppl are admitting to being druids in the same lvl range:<BR>
<BR>
/who all druid 40 44<BR>
/who all druid 45 47<BR>
/who all druid 48 50<BR>
<BR>
Now add all the numbers up. Guess what? You have over five times as many druids as wizards. MANY times I have done this and ended up seeing only 1 wizard and 40+ druids. And I think it is safe to say that there are FAR more druids that use /anon and /role than there are wizards. No way to know for sure but it wouldn't surprise me to learn that of the two teleporting classes, druids outnumber wizards by a factor of 10 to 1.<BR>
<BR>
You can modify the above commands and learn a lot about who is playing what. Its an eye opener that's for. At least mages can solo... I feel sorry for wizards.<BR>
<BR>
Sarnath<BR>
Mage of Prexus
				</font>
			</td>

